assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: YE DIGITAL Corporation provides Internet of Things (IoT) solutions in Japan. The company operates cloud application service products, such as MMCloud, an IoT platform with data storage, visualization, and analysis; and MMPredict, an AI-based fault prediction engine. It also offers MMsmartMonitor service with wireless cameras and cloud viewer; MMEye that enables real-time image inspection; MMsmartSecurity, a factory security solution for monitoring and status management; Smart Berth System, a berth monitoring system at the logistics facilities; and MMsmart BusStop, a smart bus stop cloud system. In addition, the company provides communication adapters with various communication interfaces, such as MMLink-3G communication adapters; and MMLink-Lite 3G SIM-unlocked USB interface communication adapters. Further, the company offers location aware solutions, precise indoor localization solutions, camera products, controllers, cellular network products, data loggers, programmable HMIs, and remote monitoring software, as well as IoT consulting services. It serves various industries, such as semi-conductor manufacturers, machine tool manufacturers, food manufacturers, temperature controller manufacturers, and others. The company was formerly known as Yaskawa Information Systems Corporation and changed its name to YE DIGITAL Corporation in March 2019. YE DIGITAL Corporation was incorporated in 1978 and is headquartered in Kitakyushu, Japan.
